name: Colored_Mach-Zehnder
description: Code written and edited by Trevor Donovan for his summer 2024 SULI internship at Brookhaven National Lab.  Work is on a spectroscopically resolved, single photon sensitive Mach-Zehnder interferometer setup.

name: coincidence-LMFIT
description: A set of functions for fitting Gaussian and then sine functions to channel pair coincidence distributions using the LMFIT python package. Written by Aaron Mueninghoff during the summer of 2022 for the Quantum Astrometry project at Brookhaven National Lab.
license.name: Other

name: coincidence_timestamp_qutag
description: Written by Denis Dolzhenko. Given timestamps in each of the four channels of a qutag, determines coincidences across channels.

name: Ghost_Imaging_Scripts
description: Written by Denis Dolzhenko. These scripts use Ghost Imaging Parser .txt files as input.

name: quTAG_scripts
description: Written by Denis Dolzhenko. Scripts for taking data with the original tabletop SNSV setup.

name: TPics3
description: Written by Denis Dolzhenko. Data display for Timepix3.
